windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 756 to 780?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
C) Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
options.C: Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.

windows.answer: C) Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.

windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 3160 to 3179?
A) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
B) Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
options.B: Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
